modules.description: Provides operations to create and manage SSL-wrapped network sockets, including extracting underlying file descriptors and accessing the SSL context. Works with Eio network sockets and OpenSSL contexts. Used to establish secure communication channels in network applications.

Provides asynchronous SSL socket operations, including reading, writing, and establishing secure connections. Works with eio's event loop and handles SSL contexts, sockets, and buffered data. Enables secure network communication in concurrent Eio-based applications.

Manages secure network communication by wrapping Eio sockets with SSL, enabling encrypted data transfer. Exposes operations to access underlying file descriptors and SSL contexts, facilitating low-level control and configuration. Supports establishing and managing secure channels, allowing for tasks like secure client-server interactions and custom SSL settings. Enables integration with OpenSSL for advanced cryptographic operations.
